 Summary of Introductory Article on Intranets

The article "What is an Intranet?" from Techopedia provides a clear overview of what an intranet is and its benefits for organizations. It explains that an intranet is a private network used by companies to facilitate communication and collaboration among employees. 

Key points include:
- Intranets provide a centralized location for important documents and resources.
- They enhance communication through forums, chat systems, and news updates.
- Intranets can improve productivity by streamlining workflows and providing easy access to information.

For more details, you can read the full article [here](https://www.techopedia.com/definition/30762/intranet).
